The paper presents a learning-based algorithm for medical image registration using a CNN model, which falls under computer vision (cs.CV) and machine learning (cs.LG) sub-categories. The method does not require supervised information, indicating an unsupervised learning approach, which is relevant to artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and information theory (cs.IT) sub-categories. The use of a spatial transform layer and smoothness constraints suggests a neural network-based approach, which is also relevant to neural and evolutionary computing (cs.NE) sub-category.
